title: Grateful Dead Live at Barton Hall, Cornell U on 1981-05-16
description:
Set 1

Feel Like A Stranger-> Friend Of The Devil-> Me & My Uncle-> Big River, Althea-> CC Rider, Brown Eyed Women, Passenger, High Time-> Let It Grow-> Don't Ease Me In

Set 2

Shakedown Street-> Bertha-> Lost Sailor-> Saint Of Circumstance-> Spanish Jam-> Drums-> Truckin'-> Nobody's Fault But Mine-> Stella Blue-> Goin' Down The Road Feelin' Bad-> One More Saturday Night, E: Uncle John's Band

reviews.review_text: I wuz there I remember the morning of the concert was chilly and all these Dead Heads were scattered about the campus looking for tickets. Barton Hall was the staging area for WWI cadets and had a certain old world charm to it.  While the concert may not have been the Dead's best at Cornell, it was a good one and I remember that there was a lot of crowd surfing. -JES
